The code that currently does that for other paths is `fixSourceLinks` in `manual/examples/resources/editor-settings.js` but it's not called for data scripts (script tags that are not javascript) and it wouldn't work anyway. You probably want to find the importmap script in the array of data scripts. Call `JSON.parse` on its content, then fix the paths, then replace the content of the script with`JSON.stringify`.  The paths should be fixed using `window.location` and not hard coded to `https://three....` so that you can run it locally (see `fixSourceLinks`)

