There is no support of `THREE.LOD` in both CSS renderers. Hence, a manual call of `THREE.LOD.update()` is required to update the internal state of the LOD object.

The main purpose of `THREE.LOD` is to manage geometries with different complexities which is in general not relevant for CSS renderers. Hence, the above use case seems a bit "off-label".

