I do not vote to introduce a new parameter since `autoUpdate` is already in place for solving such issues. The ideal usage would be this:
```js
scene.autoUpdate = false;

function  render() {

	scene.updateMatrixWorld();

	renderer.render( scene, camera );
	css2DRenderer.render( scene, camera );
	css3DRenderer.render( scene, camera );
}
```
`Object3D.matrixAutoUpdate` works the same. If the flag is set to true, the engine automatically performs updates no matter if the update is necessary or not (since there is no caching or dirty flags in place). If you want better performance, disable the flag and handle the update on app level. This is the current intended usage of the library.

For anyone else who comes across this, the property has since been renamed from `autoUpdate` to `matrixWorldAutoUpdate`. The solution is otherwise still valid.

```
scene.matrixWorldAutoUpdate = false;

function  render() {

	scene.updateMatrixWorld();

	renderer.render( scene, camera );
	css2DRenderer.render( scene, camera );
	css3DRenderer.render( scene, camera );
}
```

